MARY A. O’BRIEN, PROSECUTOR, v. ALBERT A. FREY AND LOUIS F. BUTTNER, ESQUIRE, RECORDER OF THE BOROUGH OF KEANSBURG, COUNTY OF MONMOUTH, STATE OF NEW JERSEY, RESPONDENTS. Argued January 22, 1926 Decided May 11, 1926.

Before Justices Tbenoitard and Katzenbach.

Eor the prosecutor, Kwrkus & Karlcus. Eor the respondents, Leo J. Warwick. Per Cubiam:.

Our examination of the affidavits discloses that there is presented by the applicant for consideration a fqirly debatable question, and, accordingly, the writ of certiorari will be allowed.
